290  /**
291   * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement}, mostly, if not exclusively, for use by {@link
292   * SyntheticAnnotationMirror} instances.
293   *
294   * @param e a non-{@code null} {@link TypeElement} whose {@link TypeElement#getKind() getKind()} method returns {@link
295   * javax.lang.model.element.ElementKind#ANNOTATION_TYPE}
296   *
297   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code e} is {@code null}
298   *
299   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if the supplied {@link TypeElement}'s {@link TypeElement#getKind() getKind()}
300   * method does not return {@link javax.lang.model.element.ElementKind#ANNOTATION_TYPE}
301   */
302  public SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(final TypeElement e) {
303    super();
304    if (e.getKind() != ANNOTATION_TYPE) {
305      throw new IllegalArgumentException("e: " + e);
306    }
307    this.annotationMirrors = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>(e.getAnnotationMirrors());
308    Name n = e.getSimpleName();
309    this.sn = n instanceof SyntheticName sn ? sn : new SyntheticName(n.toString());
310    n = e.getQualifiedName();
311    this.fqn = n instanceof SyntheticName sn ? sn : new SyntheticName(n.toString());
312    // Deliberate: Type is an inner class and hence cannot be shared
313    this.type = new Type();
314    final List<ExecutableElement> elements = methodsIn(e.getEnclosedElements());
315    if (elements.isEmpty()) {
316      this.elements = List.of();
317    } else {
318      final List<InternalAnnotationElement> elements0 = new ArrayList<>(elements.size());
319      for (final ExecutableElement ee :elements) {
320        // Deliberate: no instanceof InternalAnnotationElement check, i.e. wrapping/copying is deliberate and necessary
321        elements0.add(new InternalAnnotationElement(ee.getAnnotationMirrors(),
322                                                    ee.getReturnType(),
323                                                    ee.getSimpleName(),
324                                                    ee.getDefaultValue()));
325      }
326      this.elements = unmodifiableList(elements0);
327    }
328  }
329
330  /**
331   * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement}, mostly, if not exclusively, for use by {@link
332   * SyntheticAnnotationMirror} instances.
333   *
334   * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
335   * must not be {@code null}
336   *
337   * @param fullyQualifiedName the fully qualified name of the synthetic element; must conform to Java classname
338   * restrictions; must not be {@code null}
339   *
340   * @param elements a {@link List} of {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}s modeling the annotation elements; must not be
341   * {@code null}
342   *
343   * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
344   *
345   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if {@code fullyQualifiedName} does not conform to Java classname restrictions
346   *
347   * @see SyntheticAnnotationElement
348   *
349   * @see SyntheticAnnotationMirror
350   */
351  public SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
352                                        final SyntheticName fullyQualifiedName,
353                                        final List<? extends SyntheticAnnotationElement> elements) {
354    super();
355    this.annotationMirrors = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>(annotationMirrors);
356    final String fqn = fullyQualifiedName.toString();
357    final int i = fqn.lastIndexOf('.');
358    this.sn = i >= 0 ? new SyntheticName(fqn.substring(i + 1)) : fullyQualifiedName;
359    this.fqn = fullyQualifiedName;
360    this.type = new Type();
361    if (elements.isEmpty()) {
362      this.elements = List.of();
363    } else {
364      final List<InternalAnnotationElement> elements0 = new ArrayList<>(elements.size());
365      for (final SyntheticAnnotationElement sae : elements) {
366        elements0.add(new InternalAnnotationElement(sae.annotationMirrors(), sae.type(), sae.name(), sae.defaultValue()));
367      }
368      this.elements = unmodifiableList(elements0);
369    }
370  }

465  // See https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1
466  private static final TypeMirror validateScalarType(final TypeMirror type) {
467    if (validAnnotationInterfaceElementScalarType(type)) {
468      return type;
469    }
470    throw new IllegalArgumentException("type: " + type);
471  }

480   * An <strong>experimental</strong> collection of information out of which a synthetic annotation element may be
481   * fashioned.

483   * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson" target="_top">Laird Nelson</a>
484   *
485   * @see SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement#SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(List, SyntheticName, List)
486   */
487  public static final class SyntheticAnnotationElement {
488
489
490    /*
491     * Instance fields.

521     *

532    /**
533     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
534     *
535     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
536     * not be {@code null}
537     *
538     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
539     * {@code null}
540     *
541     * @param defaultValue a {@link SyntheticAnnotationValue} representing the default value; may be {@code null}
542     *
543     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
544     *
545     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
546     *
547     * @see #SyntheticAnnotationElement(List, TypeMirror, SyntheticName, SyntheticAnnotationValue)
548     *
549     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
550     * section 9.6.1
551     */
552    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
553                                      final SyntheticName name,
554                                      final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue) {
555      this(List.of(), type, name, defaultValue);
556    }

558    /**
559     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
560     *
561     * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
562     * must not be {@code null}
563     *
564     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
565     * not be {@code null}
566     *
567     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
568     * {@code null}
569     *
570     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
571     *
572     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
573     *
574     * @see #SyntheticAnnotationElement(List, TypeMirror, SyntheticName, SyntheticAnnotationValue)
575     *
576     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
577     * section 9.6.1
578     */
579    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
580                                      final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
581                                      final SyntheticName name) {
582      this(annotationMirrors, type, name, null);
583    }
584
585    /**
586     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
587     *
588     * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
589     * must not be {@code null}
590     *
591     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
592     * not be {@code null}
593     *
594     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
595     * {@code null}
596     *
597     * @param defaultValue a {@link SyntheticAnnotationValue} representing the default value; may be {@code null}
598     *
599     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
600     *
601     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
602     *
603     * @spec https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se25/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1 Java Language Specification,
604     * section 9.6.1
605     */
606    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
607                                      final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
608                                      final SyntheticName name,
609                                      final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue) {
610      super();
611      this.annotationMirrors = List.copyOf(annotationMirrors);
612      this.type = switch (type) {
613      case null -> throw new NullPointerException("type");
614      case ArrayType t when t.getKind() == ARRAY -> validateScalarType(t.getComponentType());
615      default -> validateScalarType(type);
616      };
617      if (name.contentEquals("getClass") || name.contentEquals("hashCode") || name.contentEquals("toString")) {
618        // java.lang.Object-declared methods that might otherwise meet annotation element requirements
619        throw new IllegalArgumentException("name: " + name);
620      }
621      this.name = name;
622      this.defaultValue = defaultValue;
623    }
624
625
626    /*
627     * Instance fields.
628     */
629
630
631    final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors() {
632      return this.annotationMirrors;
633    }
634
635    @Override // Object
636    public final boolean equals(final Object other) {
637      return this == other || switch (other) {
638      case null -> false;
639      case SyntheticAnnotationElement sae when this.getClass() == sae.getClass() ->
640      Objects.equals(this.name, sae.name) &&
641      Objects.equals(this.type, sae.type) &&
642      Objects.equals(this.annotationMirrors, sae.annotationMirrors); // TODO: hmm
643      default -> false;
644      };
645    }
646
647    @Override // Object
648    public final int hashCode() {
649      int hashCode = 31;
650      int c = this.name.hashCode();
651      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
652      c = this.type.hashCode();
653      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
654      c = this.annotationMirrors.hashCode(); // TODO: hmm
655      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
656      return hashCode;
657    }
658
659    final SyntheticName name() {
660      return this.name;
661    }
662
663    final TypeMirror type() {
664      return this.type;
665    }
666
667    final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue() {
668      return this.defaultValue;
669    }

673  /**
674   * An <strong>experimental</strong>, synthetic {@link DeclaredType} implementation that models the synthetic
675   * annotation type declared by the enclosing synthetic {@link SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement}.

677   * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson" target="_top">Laird Nelson</a>
678   *
679   * @see SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement
680   */

748  // Note: inner class, built out of SyntheticAnnotationElement instances; see getEnclosingElement()
749  private final class InternalAnnotationElement implements ExecutableElement {
750
751
752    /*
753     * Instance fields.
754     */
755
756
757    private final CopyOnWriteArrayList<AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors;
758
759    private final Type t;
760
761    private final SyntheticName name;
762
763    private final SyntheticAnnotationValue defaultValue;
764
765
766    /*
767     * Constructors.
768     */
769
770
771    private InternalAnnotationElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
772                                      final TypeMirror type,
773                                      final Name name,
774                                      final AnnotationValue defaultValue) {
775      super();
776      this.annotationMirrors = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>(annotationMirrors);
777      // This Type is NOT an inner class and cannot receive annotations so this is OK.
778      this.t = type instanceof Type t ? t : new Type(type);
779      this.name = name instanceof SyntheticName sn ? sn : new SyntheticName(name);
780      this.defaultValue =
781        defaultValue instanceof SyntheticAnnotationValue sav ? sav : new SyntheticAnnotationValue(defaultValue.getValue());
782    }
783
784
785    /*
786     * Instance fields.
787     */
788
789
790    @Override // ExecutableElement
791    public final <R, P> R accept(final ElementVisitor<R, P> v, final P p) {
792      return v.visitExecutable(this, p);
793    }
794
795    @Override // ExecutableElement
796    public final Type asType() {
797      return this.t;
798    }
799
800    @Override // ExecutableElement (AnnotatedConstruct)
801    public final List<AnnotationMirror> getAnnotationMirrors() {
802      return this.annotationMirrors;
803    }
804
805    @Override // ExecutableElement (AnnotatedConstruct)
806    public final <A extends Annotation> A getAnnotation(final Class<A> annotationType) {
807      return null; // deliberate
808    }
809
810    @Override // ExecutableElement (AnnotatedConstruct)
811    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
812    public final <A extends Annotation> A[] getAnnotationsByType(final Class<A> annotationType) {
813      return (A[])EMPTY_ANNOTATION_ARRAY; // deliberate
814    }
815
816    @Override // ExecutableElement
817    public AnnotationValue getDefaultValue() {
818      return this.defaultValue;
819    }
820
821    @Override // ExecutableElement (Element)
822    public final List<? extends Element> getEnclosedElements() {
823      return List.of();
824    }
825
826    @Override // ExecutableElement (Element)
827    public final SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement getEnclosingElement() {
828      return SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement.this;
829    }
830
831    @Override // ExecutableElement (Element)
832    public final Set<Modifier> getModifiers() {
833      return ABSTRACT_ONLY_MODIFIERS;
834    }
835
836    @Override // ExecutableElement (Element)

838      return ElementKind.METHOD;
839    }
840
841    @Override // ExecutableElement

843      return List.of();
844    }

882    /*
883     * Inner and nested classes.
884     */
885
886
887    private static final class Type implements ExecutableType {
888
889
890      /*
891       * Instance fields.
892       */
893
894
895      private final TypeMirror type;
896
897
898      /*
899       * Constructors.
900       */
901
902
903      private Type(final TypeMirror type) { // the "return type"
904        super();
905        this.type = switch (type) {
906        case null -> throw new NullPointerException("type");
907        case ArrayType t when t.getKind() == ARRAY -> validateScalarType(t.getComponentType());
908        case Type t -> t.type;
909        default -> validateScalarType(type);
910        };
911      }
912
913
914      /*
915       * Instance methods.
916       */
917
918
919      @Override // TypeMirror
920      public final <R, P> R accept(final TypeVisitor<R, P> v, final P p) {
921        return v.visitExecutable(this, p);
922      }
923
924      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
925      public final <A extends Annotation> A getAnnotation(final Class<A> annotationType) {
926        return null; // deliberate
927      }
928
929      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
930      public final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> getAnnotationMirrors() {
931        return List.of(); // can't actually put type annotations on an executable type to my knowledge
932      }
933
934      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
935      @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
936      public final <A extends Annotation> A[] getAnnotationsByType(final Class<A> annotationType) {
937      return (A[])EMPTY_ANNOTATION_ARRAY; // deliberate
938      }
939
940      @Override // ExecutableType (TypeMirror)
941      public final TypeKind getKind() {
942        return TypeKind.EXECUTABLE;
943      }
944
945      @Override // ExecutableType
946      public final List<? extends TypeMirror> getParameterTypes() {
947        return List.of();
948      }
949
950      @Override // ExecutableType
951      public final NoneType getReceiverType() {
952        return NoneType.of();
953      }
954
955      @Override // ExecutableType
956      public final TypeMirror getReturnType() {
957        return this.type;
958      }
959
960      @Override // ExecutableType
961      public final List<? extends TypeMirror> getThrownTypes() {
962        return List.of();
963      }
964
965      @Override // ExecutableType
966      public final List<? extends TypeVariable> getTypeVariables() {
967        return List.of();
968      }
969
970    }
